name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On October 21, a student from Changchun No. 2 Middle School committed suicide. Afterwards, the school installed guardrails in each class and prohibited any student from discussing the incident or posting it online. A student was found by the Internet police after posting a video on TikTok.

You thought cosplay was banned, but in fact it was cosplaying Shanghai's lockdown.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Recently, someone used AI to generate a video of "Putin's ex-wife Lyudmila" to promote products online. The video said, "Seeing Putin working hard every day, I really feel sorry for him. He has dedicated his whole life to Russia. I hope everyone will support Russian food."

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On the first anniversary of Li Keqiang's death, the Erqi Memorial Hall in Zhengzhou issued an announcement: Due to emergency repairs to fire equipment failure, the Erqi Memorial Tower in Zhengzhou will be temporarily closed from 12:00 to 17:00 on October 27.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: October 26, Shenzhen, Guangdong. Urban management officers tried to confiscate a vendor's merchandise, but the vendor, unable to bear it any longer, pulled out a kitchen knife and confronted the officers.
